1
00:00:39,310 --> 00:00:40,640
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:42,070
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:44,380
What if it were possible...

4
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:48,010
to swap only the brain
without changing the face?

5
00:00:48,750 --> 00:00:49,780
By any chance,

6
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:51,950
are you talking about you, Director?

7
00:00:54,590 --> 00:00:55,960
If it were possible,
who would I swap with?

8
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:58,390
Momo.

9
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:00,560
No way.

10
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:25,720
Looks like we're the only guys here
on our own.

11
00:01:26,150 --> 00:01:27,450
I guess it's because of your job,

12
00:01:27,820 --> 00:01:29,660
but you're always so conscious
of what others think.

13
00:01:30,660 --> 00:01:31,990
- I think that's him.
- I'm telling you, it is.

14
00:01:32,230 --> 00:01:34,190
I think that woman
over there recognizes me.

15
00:01:34,190 --> 00:01:35,760
- Right?
- She must.

16
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:36,900
A look like this is one of a kind.

17
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:40,500
Doesn't anyone recognize you?

18
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,340
Sometimes. The younger crowd, mostly.

19
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:45,540
I can't even eat out with actors.

20
00:01:45,910 --> 00:01:48,010
They're always asking
for an autograph or a picture.

21
00:01:48,470 --> 00:01:52,010
You win some, you lose some.
That's the price of fame.

22
00:01:52,810 --> 00:01:55,880
Didn't you always say
there's no such thing as a free lunch?

23
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:57,550
Yesterday, Ju Shin said...

24
00:01:58,250 --> 00:02:00,490
you and Reporter Geum looked
like a couple.

25
00:02:02,190 --> 00:02:04,820
- And?
- I told him he's way off.

26
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,130
You two must have been pretty cozy
for him to say that.

27
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:09,300
What are you talking about?

28
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:12,800
You two are like brother and sister,
while she keeps me at arm's length.

29
00:02:20,810 --> 00:02:21,810
Hey.

30
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:24,810
Do you really like Ba Ra?

31
00:02:25,580 --> 00:02:26,610
I do.

32
00:02:26,610 --> 00:02:28,510
Then stop thinking about your feelings.

33
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:30,850
If you were Ba Ra's actual brother,

34
00:02:31,380 --> 00:02:33,350
and she told you she was dating a man
23 years older than her,

35
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:35,220
would you say "That's great, go for it"?

36
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:36,790
You sound just like her actual brother.

37
00:02:37,020 --> 00:02:41,230
Loving someone means you must respect
and consider their feelings, not yours.

38
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:42,460
That's what real love is.

39
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:47,670
I think Manager Yoon is perfect for you.

40
00:02:47,670 --> 00:02:48,830
"Perfect" how?

41
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,640
There has to be a spark.

42
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:54,210
Your standards are too high from dealing
with celebrities and their wives so often.

43
00:02:54,210 --> 00:02:55,840
You're not one to talk.

44
00:02:56,610 --> 00:02:57,910
(Ju Shin)

45
00:02:58,210 --> 00:02:59,710
Momo is a commoner.

46
00:03:01,780 --> 00:03:03,720
- Yes?
- So you went to the hospital together?

47
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:06,050
- Yes.
- His phone was off.

48
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:07,520
We're having breakfast together now.

49
00:03:07,890 --> 00:03:11,020
Just as I thought, everything's fine.
Tell him he got a clean bill of health.

50
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:13,830
Okay. And tell him to cut back
on the sugary drinks.

51
00:03:14,390 --> 00:03:16,130
An upset stomach can cause headaches.

52
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:17,630
Got it. Thanks.

53
00:03:18,930 --> 00:03:19,970
Was that Director Shin?

54
00:03:24,770 --> 00:03:27,170
- Hello?
- I don't feel well.

55
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:28,340
How so?

56
00:03:28,610 --> 00:03:31,680
Could you pick up a pregnancy test
for me tonight?

57
00:03:33,210 --> 00:03:34,210
A pregnancy test.

58
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:35,880
Okay.

59
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:37,250
Talk to you later.

60
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:46,990
Did you marry when you were young?

61
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:49,060
If you thought
Kim Jin Ju was your daughter...

62
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:52,300
I wasn't married.
It was back in high school.

63
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:56,440
- She was a year older than me.
- An older girl?

64
00:03:57,340 --> 00:03:58,340
Yes.

65
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:01,510
We were young and reckless.

66
00:04:02,210 --> 00:04:03,840
She got pregnant during my senior year.

67
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:07,680
So your girlfriend gave birth
when she was 20?

68
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,550
But then my family's business went under.

69
00:04:12,220 --> 00:04:13,620
After my family went bankrupt,

70
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:17,520
she left our three-day-old baby
with me in midwinter December...

71
00:04:17,520 --> 00:04:18,520
and disappeared.

72
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:20,230
But didn't she have a family?

73
00:04:20,490 --> 00:04:23,230
Even her widowed mother, a cleaner,
didn't know where she went.

74
00:04:24,530 --> 00:04:27,300
Creditors were hounding us,
so my parents went into hiding,

75
00:04:27,470 --> 00:04:31,270
and I crashed at a friend's place
with the baby before moving to Japan.

76
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:34,140
When you came back,
did you ever hear from the baby's mother?

77
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:39,080
- You met her?
- I did.

78
00:04:39,710 --> 00:04:41,850
And? Is she doing well?

79
00:04:43,820 --> 00:04:44,820
The thing is...

80
00:04:47,150 --> 00:04:50,420
I'll tell you more once I find my child.

81
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:52,530
Is she someone I might know?

82
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,800
She has to be someone I know.

83
00:05:07,010 --> 00:05:11,410
Can you pull up a list of our clients
between the ages of 47 and 50?

84
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:13,950
- Both men and women?
- Just the women.

85
00:05:14,150 --> 00:05:15,150
Right away.

86
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:19,620
Isn't that for Kang Ma Ri?
She doesn't want it?

87
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,420
- That's right.
- What is it now?

88
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:23,060
She says it makes her arms look big.

89
00:05:23,420 --> 00:05:25,660
That's because her arms are big.

90
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,530
She should lose weight or chop them off.

91
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:29,460
She said the last one made her look
flat-chested.

92
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:31,860
She hated the Pedro dress
because it showed the top of her feet.

93
00:05:31,930 --> 00:05:33,000
She's still complaining?

94
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,000
She's the one who stepped on the dress
and fell at the press conference?

95
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:38,200
I've reached my limit.
Tell her to find another sponsor.

96
00:05:38,970 --> 00:05:39,970
Are you serious?

97
00:05:40,410 --> 00:05:41,410
Yes.

98
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:52,120
(Director Shin)

99
00:05:56,420 --> 00:05:57,420
Hello?

100
00:05:57,790 --> 00:05:58,790
Is now a good time to talk?

101
00:05:59,190 --> 00:06:01,390
- Yes.
- Do you have time to meet?

102
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:03,460
I wanted to ask you about the orphanage.

103
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,160
I'd like to get your advice.

104
00:06:06,070 --> 00:06:07,870
- Okay.
- Today.

105
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:09,770
I'm booked until the day after tomorrow.

106
00:06:10,470 --> 00:06:12,070
- Wednesday.
- Yes.

107
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:20,510
Were you right?

108
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:25,440
Goodness. Congratulations!

109
00:07:27,250 --> 00:07:28,250
Congratulations?

110
00:07:29,580 --> 00:07:31,320
You two are getting married anyway.

111
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,820
I'm not ready for that.

112
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,720
Just hurry up and have the wedding.

113
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:37,660
I don't want to have it.

114
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:43,160
Director Shin would be so happy.

115
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:44,730
Who cares?

116
00:07:45,260 --> 00:07:48,200
This is the sky's way of helping you
forget your sorrows with a new life.

117
00:07:48,370 --> 00:07:50,640
It's a gift
so that you can be happy again.

118
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:55,270
Are you saying all mothers are happy?

119
00:07:58,740 --> 00:08:00,710
If you ever need help, ask anytime.

120
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:01,750
I don't need any.

121
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:02,750
You really don't get people, do you?

122
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,720
Don't jump to conclusions.

123
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:12,160
It's not my baby.

124
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,060
How could it be mine?

125
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:20,800
- Knock before you come in.
- But the door was open.

126
00:08:21,130 --> 00:08:22,170
Close them.

127
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:58,170
Hello.

128
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:02,040
That's not me.

129
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:04,410
I heard that person quit.

130
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:08,150
What's your relationship to her?

131
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:10,280
I'm her father.

132
00:09:18,090 --> 00:09:21,230
When I saw how startled you were,
I started thinking,

133
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:23,900
and I wondered if you had some trouble
when you lived at the orphanage.

134
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:28,630
Am I right?

135
00:09:29,170 --> 00:09:30,970
After the director passed away,

136
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:35,240
have you happened to visit the orphanage?

137
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:39,480
The babies and toddlers...

138
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:42,350
are especially heartbreaking to see.

139
00:09:44,220 --> 00:09:46,320
They play some lullaby-like music,

140
00:09:46,450 --> 00:09:49,820
and it's already sad seeing
two or three babies napping together,

141
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:52,290
but imagine
if there's thunder and lightning.

142
00:09:52,620 --> 00:09:54,360
The babies get absolutely terrified.

143
00:09:55,890 --> 00:09:59,630
I wish they could hire more caregivers,
at least for the nursery.

144
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:02,170
So they're like aunts to the kids?

145
00:10:02,570 --> 00:10:03,570
Yes.

146
00:10:06,370 --> 00:10:07,410
Have some.

147
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:15,880
You don't care for wine?

148
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:19,420
No, that's not it.

149
00:10:24,420 --> 00:10:27,290
To be honest,
I don't really know much about wine.

150
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,370
May I tell you a bit more?

151
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:42,170
You know you're not supposed to
let toddlers watch things on a phone.

152
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:44,040
Of course not.

153
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,350
You should bring it up
with the office manager directly.

154
00:10:46,450 --> 00:10:49,310
I tried talking to the office manager
about it after I left.

155
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:51,820
He said they don't have
the resources for it.

156
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:55,190
I guess you don't get involved
in these matters at all.

157
00:10:55,590 --> 00:10:56,720
It's not so much that I don't.

158
00:10:58,160 --> 00:11:01,090
The office manager has been in charge
of running things since my father's day.

159
00:11:01,390 --> 00:11:02,590
And we have advisors, too.

160
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:06,430
Well, it's a relief that
you're taking an interest now.

161
00:11:06,730 --> 00:11:08,170
You make a donation every month,
don't you?

162
00:11:09,030 --> 00:11:10,340
I saw your name on the donor list.

163
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:12,810
As I mentioned last time,

164
00:11:13,310 --> 00:11:16,110
I wouldn't be where I am today
without the Nua Foundation.

165
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,980
I just want to give back
a little something...

166
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:21,950
Have you thought about quitting reporting
and taking over the orphanage?

167
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:23,780
As the director?

168
00:11:24,450 --> 00:11:27,250
- That's out of the question.
- Why is it out of the question?

169
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:28,750
You're more than qualified.

170
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:33,060
Didn't Momo tell you?

171
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:39,630
I'm leaving my job at the end
of the month to help Momo out.

172
00:11:40,430 --> 00:11:41,570
You're going to be her manager?

173
00:11:42,330 --> 00:11:43,640
You're quitting the paper for that?

174
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:46,670
She says she needs someone
who can be like family.

175
00:11:47,170 --> 00:11:48,340
That's why.

176
00:11:48,670 --> 00:11:49,880
Momo's offer...

177
00:11:50,140 --> 00:11:53,250
is for me to officially take over
and run the gallery in two to three years.

178
00:11:53,810 --> 00:11:55,110
But above all,

179
00:11:56,620 --> 00:11:58,150
I don't have anyone either.

180
00:11:58,650 --> 00:11:59,650
Are you lonely?

181
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:02,520
Why did I ask something obvious?

182
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:05,520
I have a soft spot
for people younger than me.

183
00:12:07,790 --> 00:12:09,560
So you're saying you're tough
on Yong Joong and me?

184
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:21,870
Also, it would be nice
to let the girls grow their hair out.

185
00:12:22,140 --> 00:12:25,840
- They're forbidden to?
- It's high maintenance and hard to wash.

186
00:12:32,820 --> 00:12:36,460
I was always so envious
of the girls with long hair,

187
00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:40,960
watching them braid it,
tie it up, and put in pins.

188
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:43,530
I'd find myself staring
for the longest time.

189
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:46,030
Long hair suits you.

190
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:48,270
I cut a lot off when I started this job.

191
00:12:48,270 --> 00:12:49,500
How long did it used to be?

192
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:50,940
Below my waist.

193
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,010
Do you have a picture?

194
00:13:02,150 --> 00:13:04,150
What was your mother like?

195
00:13:04,820 --> 00:13:07,690
She was incredibly devoted
to my dad and me.

196
00:13:07,690 --> 00:13:10,260
You call him "Dad" too.

197
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:11,420
Who else?

198
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:13,960
Yong Joong?

199
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:18,500
It sounds so affectionate.

200
00:13:22,430 --> 00:13:24,000
In what way was she devoted?

201
00:13:25,470 --> 00:13:26,870
She was wise, I'd say.

202
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:29,840
She never graduated from college.

203
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:33,110
She met my dad during her sophomore year,
and they got married.

204
00:13:35,550 --> 00:13:38,520
Do you take after your mother
or your father?

205
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,620
- In looks?
- In personality.

206
00:13:40,690 --> 00:13:41,820
I don't take after my father, do I?

207
00:13:44,620 --> 00:13:45,790
What's that nod for?

208
00:13:47,030 --> 00:13:48,030
No reason.

209
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:50,100
And I'm nothing like my mother, either.

210
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:55,930
You and your father visited the orphanage
when I was in elementary school.

211
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:57,840
This might sound a little strange, but...

212
00:13:58,440 --> 00:14:01,170
You were just so elegant and graceful.

213
00:14:01,970 --> 00:14:03,140
Doctor...

214
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:05,780
This might sound a little strange, but...

215
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:08,750
Your looks are kind of wasted
on just your patients.

216
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:11,150
Have you ever been scouted?

217
00:14:14,690 --> 00:14:15,890
Have I lost it all now?

218
00:14:16,390 --> 00:14:17,590
You even talk like that?

219
00:14:17,790 --> 00:14:18,820
Don't change the subject.

220
00:14:19,290 --> 00:14:20,530
Do I look worn out,
beaten down by the world?

221
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:22,460
No.

222
00:14:22,930 --> 00:14:26,030
Then and now,
you've always been hard to approach.

223
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:31,000
What's your type?

224
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:35,670
- I haven't thought about it.
- That would be a lie.

225
00:14:36,510 --> 00:14:39,040
I think most women are
pretty much the same.

226
00:14:39,310 --> 00:14:41,010
A man who's thoughtful and caring.

227
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:45,320
No. I know plenty of women
who like bad boys.

228
00:14:46,790 --> 00:14:47,820
What about me?

229
00:14:48,550 --> 00:14:49,650
The mean type?

230
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:52,020
There's a difference between being mean
and being a bad person.

231
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:54,190
And just because someone's cold
doesn't mean they're a bad person.

232
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:56,660
You do a lot of good, after all.

233
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:58,760
Through your hospital and the foundation.

234
00:15:02,130 --> 00:15:04,100
Honestly, it's overwhelming.

235
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:10,810
I'm sure most people are...

236
00:15:11,110 --> 00:15:13,150
if they're determined to live life
the right way.

237
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,120
In ten years,
I'll offer you the director's position.

238
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:30,560
We should do this from time to time.

239
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:32,760
And please continue to look after
the foundation.

240
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:34,030
Okay.

241
00:15:41,810 --> 00:15:44,540
Can we get another carpaccio?

242
00:15:44,540 --> 00:15:45,940
- Another one.
- Yes, sir.

243
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:49,350
It's nice to see you eat so well.

244
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:51,320
This is on a whole other level.

245
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:55,590
We'd sometimes get bulgogi
at the orphanage,

246
00:15:56,620 --> 00:15:59,390
but the meat didn't even seem to be
imported beef.

247
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,260
To put it bluntly,

248
00:16:01,830 --> 00:16:03,800
it was like eating stir-fried tire.

249
00:16:05,930 --> 00:16:07,330
I take back saying
we should do this again.

250
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,130
You'll bankrupt the foundation.

251
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,370
What kind of mom do you want to be?

252
00:16:14,970 --> 00:16:16,140
I'd have to get married first.

253
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,480
You're not the marrying type?

254
00:16:19,210 --> 00:16:21,080
I guess that's probably how it'll be.

255
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,010
Why so hesitant?

256
00:16:23,580 --> 00:16:26,350
- But you're so confident and smart.
- I'm just good at faking it.

257
00:16:27,950 --> 00:16:31,560
When Momo has her baby,
I'll be happy just to be its aunt.

258
00:16:33,830 --> 00:16:34,930
Let me rephrase the question.

259
00:16:36,430 --> 00:16:37,630
What kind of aunt do you want to be?

260
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:39,830
The fun aunt.

261
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:43,340
You and Momo can be the villains,

262
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,670
and I'll just be the one
who spoils the kid.

263
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:55,010
(The Humanities of Discovery)

264
00:17:00,090 --> 00:17:01,650
Looks like she's busy again today.

265
00:17:05,020 --> 00:17:07,530
I wonder what the housekeeper
left for us to eat.

266
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:37,720
Give me back my head.

267
00:17:38,260 --> 00:17:39,560
Give me back my head.

268
00:17:39,620 --> 00:17:40,730
My head...

269
00:17:51,170 --> 00:17:52,640
I am not Momo.

270
00:17:54,470 --> 00:17:56,240
This is only Momo's body.

271
00:17:56,840 --> 00:18:00,280
- What is she talking about?
- Inside my head, my brain...

272
00:18:01,410 --> 00:18:04,480
is that of Geum Ba Ra,
a reporter for the Sungwoo Daily.

273
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,180
For real?

274
00:18:07,150 --> 00:18:09,550
Everyone,
have you ever heard of a brain swap?

275
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:11,590
It is possible.

276
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:14,830
And the mastermind
with the divine touch is...

277
00:18:16,460 --> 00:18:19,000
Director Shin Ju Shin
of Nua General Hospital.

278
00:18:20,770 --> 00:18:22,830
- This is absurd.
- Seriously?

279
00:18:30,540 --> 00:18:32,510
Oh my, what is that?

280
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:34,550
Is that really the scar? No way...

281
00:18:39,990 --> 00:18:41,850
- Please, open the door!
- Director Shin!

282
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:43,890
(My daughter has a brain tumor.)

283
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,560
(Give my brain to my daughter,
Director Shin Ju Shin)

284
00:18:45,620 --> 00:18:46,730
(My older brother is brain-dead.)

285
00:18:46,730 --> 00:18:49,090
(I don't want to live,
so please save my brother, Director Shin!)

286
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:50,660
(My wife wants to die
because of her depression.)

287
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:52,530
(Her mother is in a nursing home
and could pass any day. Please, Director.)

288
00:18:52,530 --> 00:18:54,500
- Director Shin Ju Shin!
- My brother is brain-dead!

289
00:18:54,630 --> 00:18:55,830
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

290
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:57,740
Please save my mother-in-law.

291
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,940
Please, Doctor!

292
00:19:02,870 --> 00:19:07,480
- Please save my mother-in-law.
- Please save her, Director.

293
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:12,150
- Please, save her, Director!
- Director!

294
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:14,950
- Director!
- Please, help us!

295
00:19:15,090 --> 00:19:16,660
Help me, please!

296
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:31,500
Shin Ju Shin, you're under arrest
for the murder of Kim Jin Ju.

297
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:57,560
It doesn't look like
the director knows yet.

298
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:59,730
- Why didn't you tell him?
- You met him?

299
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:00,800
Yesterday.

300
00:20:01,130 --> 00:20:03,970
- Why?
- He asked about the orphanage.

301
00:20:04,340 --> 00:20:07,570
- Now that he's the foundation's chairman.
- The manager...

302
00:20:08,140 --> 00:20:10,910
He has a manager for that, doesn't he?
He can just get a report.

303
00:20:11,810 --> 00:20:14,080
There are things you can get
from a manager's report,

304
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:16,820
and things you only hear
from someone who was there.

305
00:20:20,950 --> 00:20:21,990
I'm not having it.

306
00:20:22,490 --> 00:20:23,590
That's ridiculous.

307
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:27,530
This isn't a decision
you get to make alone.

308
00:20:27,860 --> 00:20:29,990
- What if he wants me to have it?
- Obviously.

309
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:35,630
At least talk to him about it.

310
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:37,470
My life is over if I have this baby.

311
00:20:37,470 --> 00:20:39,770
Over? Not everyone gets to be a mother.

312
00:20:46,910 --> 00:20:48,050
What time do you usually go to bed?

313
00:20:48,410 --> 00:20:52,220
My articles go live early in the morning,
so I try to be in bed before midnight.

314
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:56,790
The chef is asking
if there's anything else you need.

315
00:20:59,390 --> 00:21:00,390
I'm full.

316
00:21:01,890 --> 00:21:03,900
- Check, please.
- It's already been taken care of.

317
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,400
It has?

318
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:08,500
When?

319
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:13,100
When I stepped out
to take that call earlier.

320
00:21:16,470 --> 00:21:17,640
I'm the one who asked you to dinner.

321
00:21:17,940 --> 00:21:20,210
Buying you this meal
is the least I could do.

322
00:21:20,450 --> 00:21:23,180
The Nua Children's Home
may have fed you terrible meat,

323
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:25,050
but they sure raised you right.

324
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:27,590
Next time, I'm treating you properly.

325
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:31,720
I know a great Hanwoo omakase place.
It's members-only.

326
00:21:31,890 --> 00:21:33,830
I didn't realize you were such a foodie.

327
00:21:34,230 --> 00:21:35,390
I wouldn't say I'm a foodie.

328
00:21:36,060 --> 00:21:37,300
What do you do for stress?

329
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:39,960
Just working is how I relieve stress.

330
00:21:40,230 --> 00:21:41,930
If you're that satisfied with your job,

331
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:43,770
you can't just quit.

332
00:21:44,340 --> 00:21:47,610
If I were the one
who desperately needed help,

333
00:21:47,940 --> 00:21:49,370
I'd be heartbroken
if someone turned their back on me.

334
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:52,880
Do you trust people?

335
00:21:53,410 --> 00:21:54,710
I have to, at first.

336
00:21:57,780 --> 00:21:59,750
But I never want to be betrayed.

337
00:22:01,050 --> 00:22:02,050
What if they do?

338
00:22:02,850 --> 00:22:03,860
What happens then?

339
00:22:06,290 --> 00:22:07,690
I cut them out of my heart.

340
00:22:09,990 --> 00:22:11,030
I'd better be careful.

341
00:22:34,490 --> 00:22:36,650
- Yes, Director Shin.
- When are you free?

342
00:22:37,220 --> 00:22:38,520
I need to make
a reservation at the restaurant.

343
00:22:40,090 --> 00:22:42,490
Can I check my schedule and text you?

344
00:22:43,390 --> 00:22:45,200
Is it your bedtime?

345
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:48,600
- Sorry.
- No, not yet.

346
00:22:49,030 --> 00:22:50,670
What about you, Director Shin?
What time do you go to bed?

347
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:53,540
I'm wide awake at this hour.

348
00:23:00,810 --> 00:23:03,150
(Momo)

349
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:07,520
- Yes.
- Can I come up?

350
00:23:09,750 --> 00:23:10,890
Is something wrong?

351
00:23:13,590 --> 00:23:14,930
I'm pregnant.

352
00:23:17,530 --> 00:23:19,500
I was feeling off,
so I took a pregnancy test.

353
00:23:20,570 --> 00:23:21,600
Are you sure?

354
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,900
Those can be inaccurate.

355
00:23:27,210 --> 00:23:29,570
If it's positive,
we should terminate it, right?

356
00:23:33,550 --> 00:23:34,550
No.

357
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:38,980
I just had surgery,
and I've been on all these antibiotics...

358
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:40,850
They're still born
perfectly normal and healthy.

359
00:23:43,250 --> 00:23:44,820
- What if...
- Don't even go there.

360
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:47,530
You're having the baby.

361
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:53,460
It'll be bad for our public image...

362
00:23:53,460 --> 00:23:54,830
We're publicly engaged.

363
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:57,400
You're having the baby.

364
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:01,470
You don't seem very happy.

365
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:09,080
I'm just in shock. I wasn't expecting it.

366
00:24:09,550 --> 00:24:11,850
It doesn't even feel like my baby.

367
00:24:12,650 --> 00:24:13,790
By that logic,

368
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:15,820
are you never going to have kids?

369
00:24:17,660 --> 00:24:19,720
I'm not ready for this now.

370
00:24:20,330 --> 00:24:22,130
I've never even thought about it.

371
00:24:23,460 --> 00:24:25,230
Then start thinking and preparing now.

372
00:24:26,230 --> 00:24:27,730
And you must be diligent
with your prenatal care.

373
00:24:39,380 --> 00:24:40,510
I'll be more attentive.

374
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:44,250
I had a scary dream
when I was waking up from the anesthesia.

375
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:46,880
I guess it was a conception dream.

376
00:24:49,450 --> 00:24:50,460
What dream?

377
00:25:01,230 --> 00:25:02,230
Paul.

378
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:08,440
I saw this outfit and thought of you.

379
00:25:08,940 --> 00:25:10,880
I thought it would look amazing on you.

380
00:25:11,140 --> 00:25:13,540
Thank you, but I can't just accept this.

381
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:16,210
Clothes are all I have to give.

382
00:25:16,780 --> 00:25:19,280
It was sponsored for one of my actors,
so it's not new.

383
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:21,590
It'll just collect dust in my closet.

384
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:23,250
A huge movie star wore this.

385
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:27,390
(Seoul)

386
00:25:34,230 --> 00:25:36,800
Are you planning to stay single forever?

387
00:25:39,140 --> 00:25:40,140
Yes.

388
00:25:40,570 --> 00:25:43,440
But we're both in our prime.

389
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:51,880
I can't trust women.

390
00:25:52,820 --> 00:25:54,190
They're just not trustworthy.

391
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:58,660
They'll leave you in a heartbeat
if they think you've got nothing to offer.

392
00:25:59,020 --> 00:26:00,560
That's not always true.

393
00:26:01,530 --> 00:26:04,560
There are plenty of kind,
wonderful women out there.

394
00:26:06,330 --> 00:26:08,730
Have you ever seen a fortune teller?

395
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:11,870
Is any of that stuff ever right?

396
00:26:12,270 --> 00:26:13,540
They can be.

397
00:26:13,810 --> 00:26:14,910
So what did they say about you?

398
00:26:15,210 --> 00:26:17,240
That I'm destined to get married
within five years,

399
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:20,280
and that my soulmate is a younger woman,
old enough to be my daughter.

400
00:26:20,610 --> 00:26:23,550
- Really?
- And then she appeared right before me.

401
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:27,450
- A young woman?
- Yes.

402
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:28,520
And then what?

403
00:26:31,090 --> 00:26:33,390
After agonizing over it by myself,
I decided to let it go.

404
00:26:33,660 --> 00:26:36,060
Why? It could've been fate.

405
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:38,760
I don't think so.
She doesn't see me that way at all.

406
00:26:40,630 --> 00:26:42,230
Well, they did say five years.

407
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:44,570
You should wait and see.

408
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:47,870
You never know what life has in store.

409
00:26:48,370 --> 00:26:50,010
Take Kim Jin Ju, for example.

410
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,980
And CEO Hyun Ran Hee, too.

411
00:26:55,580 --> 00:26:57,480
You've met CEO Hyun, right?

412
00:26:57,980 --> 00:26:59,980
She asked for your number,
so I gave it to her.

413
00:27:00,750 --> 00:27:01,750
Yes.

414
00:27:02,490 --> 00:27:03,820
Did she buy one of your pieces?

415
00:27:06,990 --> 00:27:07,990
Yes.

416
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,530
By the way,

417
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:13,630
can't you tell me who your first love was?

418
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:15,330
I won't tell a soul.

419
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:19,870
Some other time.

420
00:27:22,170 --> 00:27:23,340
Are you still looking for your child?

421
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:24,980
I'll never give up.

422
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:28,450
As long as my child is alive.

423
00:27:30,180 --> 00:27:31,220
Somehow.

424
00:27:31,520 --> 00:27:32,850
Do you know the exact time
your child was born?

425
00:27:33,890 --> 00:27:34,890
If you do...

426
00:27:35,650 --> 00:27:37,020
Well, I'm not talking
about some divine act,

427
00:27:38,660 --> 00:27:41,530
but a fortune teller might be able
to find something out for you.

428
00:27:50,770 --> 00:27:51,800
Hey, Yong Joong.

429
00:27:52,270 --> 00:27:55,270
- Did you pick up Pickles?
- Yes, the housekeeper was just leaving.

430
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:56,710
You should've just waited.

431
00:27:57,380 --> 00:27:58,410
I'm on my way now.

432
00:27:58,840 --> 00:28:01,310
I'm at Momo's place.
I wanted to show her Pickles.

433
00:28:05,550 --> 00:28:06,580
You should come, too.

434
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:09,320
No, it's okay.

435
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:14,360
I'm sure Momo won't mind. I'll ask her.

436
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,460
Pickles.

437
00:28:18,060 --> 00:28:20,530
You're so fancy.
Why would anyone abandon you?

438
00:28:26,870 --> 00:28:29,140
Momo says we should all order some food.

439
00:28:40,750 --> 00:28:42,090
(Today was another tough day.)

440
00:29:13,250 --> 00:29:15,190
Today was another tough day.

441
00:29:16,050 --> 00:29:18,320
No one talked to me,

442
00:29:18,620 --> 00:29:22,460
and even though I got first place,
my homeroom teacher didn't praise me.

443
00:29:23,030 --> 00:29:25,300
She was probably hoping
Park Ji Ah would take first.

444
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:29,830
Whenever I feel sad or treated unfairly...

445
00:29:30,270 --> 00:29:32,800
and heartbreaking tears
well up in my eyes,

446
00:29:33,300 --> 00:29:35,810
I get through it
by thinking of Yong Joong.

447
00:29:36,740 --> 00:29:38,410
His warm embrace...

448
00:29:39,010 --> 00:29:40,610
is unforgettable.

449
00:29:41,150 --> 00:29:43,210
The warmth has been etched
into my very soul.

450
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:45,920
I'll become someone amazing...

451
00:29:46,680 --> 00:29:48,220
and then go see him again.

452
00:30:22,190 --> 00:30:23,190
Are we going out to eat?

453
00:30:23,850 --> 00:30:24,860
No.

454
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,210
Welcome.

455
00:30:43,270 --> 00:30:44,280
Oh my.

456
00:30:46,540 --> 00:30:47,680
You shouldn't have.

457
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:49,650
I saw a flower shop in the building.

458
00:30:49,850 --> 00:30:52,250
This is perfect.
I was all out of flowers and dessert.

459
00:30:54,090 --> 00:30:55,250
There's a vase in the kitchen.

460
00:30:57,860 --> 00:30:58,860
Put this in the fridge.

461
00:31:02,890 --> 00:31:04,300
We can have that for dessert.

462
00:31:05,830 --> 00:31:06,830
Please, have a seat.

463
00:31:12,500 --> 00:31:13,700
Look how much he likes you.

464
00:31:14,670 --> 00:31:15,710
Hey, Pickles.

465
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:20,810
That breed's pretty rare here, isn't it?

466
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:23,480
Yes.

467
00:31:24,850 --> 00:31:25,850
What are you in the mood for?

468
00:31:26,120 --> 00:31:27,950
There's a place
that has great eel rice bowls.

469
00:31:28,420 --> 00:31:29,620
I'll leave it up to you, Momo.

470
00:31:30,250 --> 00:31:31,590
I'm not a picky eater.

471
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:33,790
I'm so bad at deciding.

472
00:31:34,390 --> 00:31:36,090
- Ba Ra!
- I'll do it.

473
00:31:49,610 --> 00:31:50,670
And some sushi, too.

474
00:31:51,240 --> 00:31:52,240
For two.

475
00:31:55,910 --> 00:31:57,210
Does Pickles eat salmon?

476
00:31:57,780 --> 00:31:58,780
He does.

477
00:32:03,150 --> 00:32:05,020
You must be a total pro at games.

478
00:32:05,460 --> 00:32:06,560
I wouldn't go that far.

479
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:09,930
Developing them is different
from playing them for fun.

480
00:32:10,490 --> 00:32:12,000
I'm terrible at games.

481
00:32:13,160 --> 00:32:14,430
I can't act.

482
00:32:16,500 --> 00:32:20,370
Company helps me laugh and feel at ease.
It really does.

483
00:32:21,140 --> 00:32:23,040
But I can't just invite anyone over,
you know?

484
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:28,150
Apparently, a hidden camera was installed
at my friend Yoo Kyung's place.

485
00:32:28,910 --> 00:32:30,980
Don't tell me it was an acquaintance
who put it there.

486
00:32:33,650 --> 00:32:37,520
Apparently, the housekeeper always watched
any repairmen who came over.

487
00:32:38,620 --> 00:32:41,060
So now, Yoo Kyung doesn't invite
anyone over anymore.

488
00:32:41,430 --> 00:32:42,990
She only attends parties outside her home.

489
00:32:43,730 --> 00:32:45,230
It might look glamorous on the outside,

490
00:32:46,060 --> 00:32:49,570
but it's an exhausting and lonely job.

491
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:54,410
Mr. Ha.

492
00:32:55,210 --> 00:32:59,440
I'm just going to call you Yong Joong
from now on.

493
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:00,640
Let's drop the formalities.

494
00:33:01,350 --> 00:33:04,280
"Mr. Ha" makes me uncomfortable too.

495
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:08,350
I bet you get to do everything
you want in life.

496
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:11,490
Is there...

497
00:33:11,990 --> 00:33:13,260
anything you've wanted to do?

498
00:33:13,890 --> 00:33:18,100
I'd love to just drive to the coast,
like in Gangwon Province.

499
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:20,630
Then you should go.

500
00:33:21,270 --> 00:33:22,570
I'm not confident enough.

501
00:33:23,170 --> 00:33:24,840
I've only ever pretended to drive
for a role.

502
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:28,910
And Director Shin Ju Shin
is always so busy.

503
00:33:30,170 --> 00:33:31,880
Let's go today for some driving practice.

504
00:33:38,980 --> 00:33:41,190
I have to watch Pickles.

505
00:33:42,950 --> 00:33:45,020
Is it about a three-hour drive
to Gangneung?

506
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:46,920
There's no traffic at night.

507
00:33:50,190 --> 00:33:52,030
Pickles, let's go.

508
00:33:52,230 --> 00:33:53,430
At least eat dinner first.

509
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:06,610
I'm almost there. Be ready to go out.

510
00:34:09,280 --> 00:34:10,450
Ju Shin is on his way.

511
00:34:10,950 --> 00:34:13,120
He told me to get ready
because we're going out.

512
00:34:13,380 --> 00:34:15,850
- A restaurant?
- Then he would've asked if I'd eaten.

513
00:34:21,630 --> 00:34:23,260
We should get going.

514
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:27,500
- At least say hi.
- You can't freeze sushi, so take it.

515
00:34:30,830 --> 00:34:32,970
I can't pick an outfit
if I don't know where we're going.

516
00:34:40,110 --> 00:34:43,010
You can go to Gangwon Province anytime.

517
00:34:49,750 --> 00:34:51,760
At least you got to see each other...

518
00:34:54,660 --> 00:34:55,660
Hello?

519
00:34:58,660 --> 00:34:59,700
Yes, speaking.

520
00:35:02,830 --> 00:35:04,200
I'm not doing any interviews.

521
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:08,670
I just said she was my cousin back then.

522
00:35:12,910 --> 00:35:13,940
I'm sorry.

523
00:35:14,780 --> 00:35:16,280
How about we grab a meal sometime instead?

524
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,310
It will be my treat.

525
00:35:19,620 --> 00:35:20,620
Okay.

526
00:35:22,550 --> 00:35:23,550
All right.

527
00:35:29,490 --> 00:35:30,490
Water.

528
00:35:59,820 --> 00:36:01,990
- Hungry?
- Not really.

529
00:36:02,260 --> 00:36:04,630
Then why are you cutting it?
Momo is going out too.

530
00:36:07,430 --> 00:36:08,470
I'm going to freeze it.

531
00:36:10,100 --> 00:36:12,670
Don't worry.
I don't like Shine Muscat cake.

532
00:36:20,780 --> 00:36:21,910
That's not what I meant.

533
00:36:23,310 --> 00:36:24,320
What do you mean?

534
00:36:45,500 --> 00:36:46,500
Is that how you do it?

535
00:36:49,710 --> 00:36:50,710
Let me do it.

536
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,110
Wash your hands first.

537
00:37:13,730 --> 00:37:14,930
Should we get going?

538
00:37:38,060 --> 00:37:40,060
I think Pickles has to go...

539
00:37:46,900 --> 00:37:50,300
- You're were here?
- Yes, with Yong Joong.

540
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:53,140
It looks like he needs to go.

541
00:37:53,700 --> 00:37:55,270
Just put a pad down for him
in the bathroom.

542
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:22,100
- Thank you.
- No problem.

543
00:38:22,870 --> 00:38:24,000
Where are we going?

544
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,500
For an ultrasound.

545
00:38:28,040 --> 00:38:29,270
I guess you guys ordered dinner?

546
00:38:30,070 --> 00:38:31,070
Then eat before you go.

547
00:38:34,310 --> 00:38:35,610
Put something down for him
in the bathroom.

548
00:38:49,090 --> 00:38:50,190
Did you guys know I was coming?

549
00:38:50,530 --> 00:38:52,000
We ordered plenty for four.

550
00:38:54,970 --> 00:38:55,970
Are you not feeling well?

551
00:39:05,980 --> 00:39:07,080
We're going for a pregnancy ultrasound.

552
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:17,250
Aren't you going to use any sauce?

553
00:39:31,470 --> 00:39:32,700
This is so embarrassing.

554
00:39:37,510 --> 00:39:38,540
The car's in the basement.

555
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:43,710
I called a cab.

556
00:39:45,780 --> 00:39:46,780
Why?

557
00:39:47,250 --> 00:39:49,850
His fur gets everywhere.
And he might scratch your expensive car.

558
00:39:50,020 --> 00:39:51,150
It's not like it's his first time
in my car.

559
00:39:56,590 --> 00:39:57,690
Are you upset about something?

560
00:39:59,230 --> 00:40:00,230
No.

561
00:40:01,930 --> 00:40:03,630
I'll keep him over the weekend.

562
00:40:04,330 --> 00:40:05,340
Hold on.

563
00:40:05,770 --> 00:40:06,970
My cab is here.

564
00:40:17,980 --> 00:40:19,680
(Nua General Hospital)

565
00:40:21,520 --> 00:40:25,590
(Congratulations on this new life!)

566
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:27,160
This will feel a little cold.

567
00:40:48,050 --> 00:40:50,610
(Pet-friendly ride)

568
00:41:08,900 --> 00:41:11,400
You know most drivers don't like
having dogs in their cars.

569
00:41:11,740 --> 00:41:14,140
There's a special taxi service for dogs.

570
00:41:14,870 --> 00:41:16,040
They have taxis like that?

571
00:41:16,340 --> 00:41:17,410
Yes.

572
00:41:22,110 --> 00:41:23,480
The doors are closing.

573
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:29,090
You're just going to leave me?

574
00:41:32,560 --> 00:41:35,190
You came all this way.
Come up and have some fruit.

575
00:41:39,100 --> 00:41:43,100
(Jaeil Apartments)

576
00:41:43,670 --> 00:41:45,300
The doors are closing.

577
00:41:50,170 --> 00:41:51,980
Pickles. Wait.

578
00:41:55,610 --> 00:41:56,650
Wet wipes.

579
00:42:11,460 --> 00:42:12,560
You'll spoil him.

580
00:42:14,130 --> 00:42:15,500
I don't give him one when we're alone.

581
00:42:24,370 --> 00:42:25,510
Do you like strawberry cake?

582
00:42:26,210 --> 00:42:27,210
Mango cake?

583
00:42:27,340 --> 00:42:28,380
Yes.

584
00:42:29,980 --> 00:42:31,210
Strawberry? Mango?

585
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:32,880
Both.

586
00:42:35,090 --> 00:42:36,090
Look at me.

587
00:42:40,290 --> 00:42:42,230
I know what you're upset about.

588
00:42:43,830 --> 00:42:44,830
But don't get me wrong.

589
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:46,260
That goes for you.

590
00:42:47,200 --> 00:42:48,270
I'm the one getting it wrong?

591
00:42:49,370 --> 00:42:51,640
I just don't like Shine Muscat cake.

592
00:42:52,470 --> 00:42:53,940
But you added, "Don't worry."

593
00:42:54,940 --> 00:42:55,940
I don't know.

594
00:42:56,970 --> 00:42:58,640
It's just what I said in the moment.

595
00:43:04,610 --> 00:43:07,380
Reporter Geum Ba Ra, you're difficult
when you get like this.

596
00:43:09,250 --> 00:43:10,720
You're clearly in a bad mood.

597
00:43:11,620 --> 00:43:14,190
It's so obvious,
but you just keep saying you're fine.

598
00:43:15,430 --> 00:43:17,030
Am I supposed to be smiling all the time?

599
00:43:17,990 --> 00:43:20,330
I wasn't saying
you couldn't have any cake.

600
00:43:21,160 --> 00:43:23,370
I just meant we should all share it.

601
00:43:25,570 --> 00:43:26,570
I know.

602
00:43:33,640 --> 00:43:36,180
Don't look.
You had a taste. That's enough.

603
00:43:38,950 --> 00:43:40,850
I feel like you treat Pickles better
than you treat me.

604
00:43:42,390 --> 00:43:43,790
How could you say that?

605
00:43:49,160 --> 00:43:51,930
Just be straight with me.
Tell me what's going on.

606
00:43:56,470 --> 00:43:57,570
Momo hates flowers.

607
00:43:57,830 --> 00:43:59,270
I'm the one who bought her
the pregnancy test.

608
00:43:59,770 --> 00:44:02,440
You were so excited to see Momo,
with no idea she was pregnant,

609
00:44:02,510 --> 00:44:05,040
that you brought her flowers and a cake,
which you never do for anyone.

610
00:44:07,440 --> 00:44:08,980
I just felt a little bad for her,
that's all.

611
00:44:12,380 --> 00:44:13,380
That's it?

612
00:44:19,620 --> 00:44:21,560
Once you see her living happily
with Ju Shin,

613
00:44:22,790 --> 00:44:25,460
you'll be able to let go and feel at ease.

614
00:44:27,300 --> 00:44:29,930
I'll admit, I was a little surprised.
I never saw it coming.

615
00:44:31,870 --> 00:44:35,440
But it's perfectly normal
for an engaged couple to have a baby.

616
00:44:44,080 --> 00:44:45,080
You big baby.

617
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:48,150
Stop being so sulky.

618
00:44:48,750 --> 00:44:49,790
You're starting to scare me.

619
00:44:52,060 --> 00:44:53,060
There's that smile.

620
00:44:55,230 --> 00:44:58,090
When the baby's born,
what will the kid call you?

621
00:44:58,560 --> 00:45:00,330
Mister? Uncle?

622
00:45:01,260 --> 00:45:03,300
Uncle, mister, whatever.

623
00:45:04,940 --> 00:45:07,300
- Time to go.
- Can't I stay?

624
00:45:07,540 --> 00:45:08,910
I know you're not serious.

625
00:45:09,910 --> 00:45:11,010
I am serious.

626
00:45:11,640 --> 00:45:14,510
I really do want to sleep over
with Pickles.

627
00:45:15,280 --> 00:45:16,280
Be my guest.

628
00:45:16,850 --> 00:45:18,350
But you don't have a change of clothes.

629
00:45:21,220 --> 00:45:24,490
I wonder if Momo's baby
will be a boy or a girl.

630
00:45:26,320 --> 00:45:29,460
If it's a girl,
Ju Shin will probably soften up.

631
00:45:30,930 --> 00:45:33,430
He was so good to Momo in the beginning.

632
00:45:34,870 --> 00:45:36,970
Isn't that because his father passed away?

633
00:45:37,870 --> 00:45:39,500
After all, he's still in mourning.

634
00:45:40,840 --> 00:45:41,840
That could be it.

635
00:45:50,010 --> 00:45:51,920
I hold all the cards now, don't I?

636
00:45:55,050 --> 00:45:56,920
I should start keeping a change of clothes
in my car.

637
00:45:57,650 --> 00:45:59,690
People would get the wrong idea
if I kept a set for you here?

638
00:46:05,430 --> 00:46:08,330
- The doors are closing.
- The wrong idea? From who?

639
00:46:08,530 --> 00:46:10,470
Some of my reporter friends
come over sometimes.

640
00:46:11,100 --> 00:46:12,200
If they were to see them...

641
00:46:12,600 --> 00:46:14,140
And here I thought
I was your only close friend.

642
00:46:14,910 --> 00:46:17,110
Momo stops by sometimes too.

643
00:46:20,510 --> 00:46:22,350
Since when did you care
what other people think?

644
00:46:23,080 --> 00:46:25,880
You have to.
The world doesn't always go my way.

645
00:46:27,780 --> 00:46:30,120
Then I'll take the heat.
Move into my place.

646
00:46:35,360 --> 00:46:36,930
I really can't seem to make myself leave.

647
00:46:41,830 --> 00:46:42,830
Go on inside.

648
00:47:00,620 --> 00:47:01,950
Try to get some proper sleep this weekend.

649
00:47:03,850 --> 00:47:04,850
You look exhausted.

650
00:47:09,230 --> 00:47:10,230
What?

651
00:47:14,660 --> 00:47:16,600
You want me to get off? Stay?

652
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:20,400
Hey...

653
00:47:22,110 --> 00:47:23,110
Yes?

654
00:47:23,540 --> 00:47:24,540
The thing is...

655
00:47:26,710 --> 00:47:27,980
I guess I was sulking.

656
00:47:29,410 --> 00:47:33,280
- I knew it!
- You treat Momo better than me.

657
00:47:33,580 --> 00:47:34,650
I was jealous and upset.

658
00:48:06,950 --> 00:48:09,290
It's wonderful to see you. Welcome.

659
00:48:09,590 --> 00:48:11,250
The lucky draw is over here.

660
00:48:11,860 --> 00:48:12,860
Okay.

661
00:48:13,520 --> 00:48:15,090
Hi! I'm a huge fan.

662
00:48:16,460 --> 00:48:17,460
Thank you.

663
00:48:20,260 --> 00:48:21,460
(Korea and Arnia 28th Anniversary
Cultural Exchange Festival)

664
00:48:25,640 --> 00:48:28,410
- You're so stunning today.
- Thank you for coming.

665
00:48:28,670 --> 00:48:31,470
You always radiate such beauty and energy.

666
00:48:31,840 --> 00:48:34,340
It's lit up here with your bright energy.

667
00:48:36,310 --> 00:48:39,250
It's been a while
since we last saw each other, hasn't it?

668
00:48:39,250 --> 00:48:41,820
Yes, indeed. So good to see you again.

669
00:48:41,890 --> 00:48:43,890
- Me too.
- Please come in.

670
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:48,460
(Korea and Arnia 28th Anniversary
Cultural Exchange Festival)

671
00:48:54,860 --> 00:48:55,870
(Director Shin Ju Shin,
Nua General Hospital)

672
00:49:07,240 --> 00:49:08,240
Director Shin.

673
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:10,010
Yes, Minister.

674
00:49:10,780 --> 00:49:12,350
I'm surprised to see you.
I know how busy you are.

675
00:49:12,750 --> 00:49:14,620
You're the ambassador's personal doctor?

676
00:49:14,620 --> 00:49:15,650
Yes.

677
00:49:16,690 --> 00:49:17,690
This is Minister Yu Jong Won.

678
00:49:18,990 --> 00:49:21,720
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- The pleasure is all mine.

679
00:49:23,360 --> 00:49:25,100
- And your wife?
- She's already inside.

680
00:49:25,800 --> 00:49:27,300
You're even more beautiful in person.

681
00:49:28,230 --> 00:49:30,430
- Thank you.
- We'll head inside after saying hello.

682
00:49:30,570 --> 00:49:31,570
Of course.

683
00:49:33,740 --> 00:49:35,340
Hello, Ba Ra.

684
00:49:36,940 --> 00:49:39,340
- How are you?
- I'm fine. Good to see you again.

685
00:49:39,340 --> 00:49:42,210
Yes, me too. I'm so happy to be in Korea.

686
00:49:49,420 --> 00:49:50,790
Doctor Shin.

687
00:49:52,060 --> 00:49:53,060
Thank you for inviting.

688
00:49:53,890 --> 00:49:54,890
This is Momo.

689
00:49:56,190 --> 00:49:57,230
It's a pleasure to meet you, sir.

690
00:49:57,560 --> 00:49:58,930
Please come in.

691
00:50:08,870 --> 00:50:10,170
- See you again.
- See you later.

692
00:50:12,480 --> 00:50:14,010
Hey!

693
00:50:15,040 --> 00:50:16,050
Momo's here.

694
00:50:17,580 --> 00:50:19,780
- Ms. Kim.
- Director!

695
00:50:20,050 --> 00:50:23,320
- Fancy seeing you here.
- You transferred to Sekyung? Yes.

696
00:50:25,860 --> 00:50:27,960
- You made it.
- Are you close with the Ambassador?

697
00:50:28,730 --> 00:50:30,860
We see each other now and then.
I've even been invited to the residence.

698
00:50:31,900 --> 00:50:33,760
- Go on in.
- Actually, I have to go.

699
00:50:34,100 --> 00:50:35,130
Why?

700
00:50:35,370 --> 00:50:37,200
I have an important meeting for a story.

701
00:50:42,410 --> 00:50:44,170
You should've taken
your English classes more seriously.

702
00:50:44,910 --> 00:50:47,210
Plenty of people can't speak English
even after four years at school.

703
00:50:48,340 --> 00:50:49,980
Get an English tutor immediately.

704
00:50:49,980 --> 00:50:51,450
You need to have some grit,

705
00:50:52,750 --> 00:50:53,750
like Ba Ra.

706
00:50:55,550 --> 00:50:56,850
Are you saying I don't have any grit?

707
00:50:57,250 --> 00:50:58,760
You both grew up in the same environment,

708
00:50:59,220 --> 00:51:00,660
but Ba Ra is fluent, isn't she?

709
00:51:04,760 --> 00:51:07,000
(NUA)

710
00:51:20,380 --> 00:51:21,380
I'm sorry.

711
00:51:22,310 --> 00:51:23,610
Can you just write anywhere?

712
00:51:23,980 --> 00:51:26,620
You can perform surgery anywhere
as long as you have your tools, right?

713
00:51:26,780 --> 00:51:28,150
That's only possible
because it's physical work.

714
00:51:31,250 --> 00:51:33,720
I have a hard time
just writing a birthday card.

715
00:51:35,090 --> 00:51:37,290
And I'd be terrified
just holding a scalpel.

716
00:51:46,170 --> 00:51:49,670
(Nua Children's Home)

717
00:51:59,150 --> 00:52:00,150
(Infants and Toddlers)

718
00:52:18,070 --> 00:52:19,070
(Ju Shin)

719
00:52:26,710 --> 00:52:28,080
Breathe.

720
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:30,410
And rotate.

721
00:52:31,880 --> 00:52:34,680
Keep your shoulders still.
Now, deep breath in.

722
00:52:34,750 --> 00:52:36,090
- Almost there.
- Okay.

723
00:52:36,350 --> 00:52:37,950
There you go.

724
00:52:38,520 --> 00:52:40,720
Okay, that's it.

725
00:52:43,060 --> 00:52:44,960
We've decided to grant you
a one-year leave of absence,

726
00:52:45,300 --> 00:52:47,200
so take that time to think things over
and then decide.

727
00:52:51,830 --> 00:52:52,840
Okay.

728
00:52:53,440 --> 00:52:54,700
How about we get married
at the vacation house?

729
00:52:57,210 --> 00:52:58,210
There are no wedding venues available.

730
00:52:59,240 --> 00:53:01,210
The high-end hotels are fully booked
until the end of next year.

731
00:53:02,850 --> 00:53:04,150
I don't want an outdoor wedding.

732
00:53:05,320 --> 00:53:07,020
I don't care if we wait.
I want it to be at the Sera Hotel.

733
00:53:07,620 --> 00:53:08,650
Does it have to be the Sera Hotel?

734
00:53:08,850 --> 00:53:10,220
They say the photos are great there.

735
00:53:11,650 --> 00:53:12,720
After the baby's born?

736
00:53:13,220 --> 00:53:14,320
I lost...

737
00:53:14,720 --> 00:53:15,790
the baby.

738
00:53:17,390 --> 00:53:18,390
What do you mean you lost it?

739
00:53:19,460 --> 00:53:20,460
I had a miscarriage.

740
00:53:26,340 --> 00:53:27,340
When?

741
00:53:30,740 --> 00:53:31,740
Why didn't you tell me?

742
00:53:32,710 --> 00:53:35,810
You have surgery every single day.
I was afraid it would throw you off.

743
00:53:36,680 --> 00:53:37,710
Besides, it's not exactly good news.

744
00:53:40,050 --> 00:53:41,250
We can always try again.

745
00:53:45,090 --> 00:53:46,090
Which hospital?

746
00:53:48,320 --> 00:53:49,390
Why didn't you come to me?

747
00:53:51,430 --> 00:53:52,430
Why didn't you tell me?

748
00:54:04,810 --> 00:54:07,310
How dare you lie to me?

749
00:54:08,210 --> 00:54:09,210
Lie?

750
00:54:10,250 --> 00:54:11,280
Why would I?

751
00:54:12,010 --> 00:54:14,320
Then name the hospital. Why can't you?

752
00:54:14,380 --> 00:54:17,650
If you can't trust me, how can we marry?

753
00:54:17,650 --> 00:54:18,720
That's my point.

754
00:54:20,260 --> 00:54:21,690
You have to act trustworthy
if you want to be trusted.

755
00:54:23,060 --> 00:54:26,100
Director Park Sun Jung.
You know her, right?

756
00:54:27,360 --> 00:54:29,100
She promised she'd keep it confidential.

757
00:54:33,970 --> 00:54:34,970
Is this who you really are?

758
00:54:35,940 --> 00:54:37,170
Do you think I'm a pushover and a joke?

759
00:54:37,810 --> 00:54:39,540
I have dignity, you know.

760
00:54:39,610 --> 00:54:41,410
Then you should've just told me
the truth from the start.

761
00:54:42,180 --> 00:54:43,680
How can you enjoy strawberries right now?

762
00:54:44,380 --> 00:54:45,380
Like nothing's wrong?

763
00:54:45,450 --> 00:54:48,920
Yes. I must be low on Vitamin C
because they're delicious.

764
00:54:50,250 --> 00:54:51,350
This is really pissing me off.

765
00:54:53,720 --> 00:54:54,720
You're pissed off?

766
00:54:55,490 --> 00:54:56,560
Would I feel good after getting hit?

767
00:54:57,090 --> 00:54:58,160
If I did, I'd be a sicko.

768
00:54:58,800 --> 00:55:00,030
It's not like I'm the one who's pregnant.

769
00:55:01,200 --> 00:55:03,430
You're right. I think it's for the best.

770
00:55:05,570 --> 00:55:06,640
Check for yourself.

771
00:55:10,440 --> 00:55:12,010
She said I could call her anytime.

772
00:55:13,040 --> 00:55:14,610
You should've been worried
and asked if I was okay first.

773
00:55:18,350 --> 00:55:21,920
Don't tell me you think
we cooked this up together.

774
00:55:23,590 --> 00:55:24,690
This isn't just some minor issue.

775
00:55:25,250 --> 00:55:26,760
Was this something you should have
handled by yourself?

776
00:55:26,890 --> 00:55:30,560
That shows how much she thought of you.
She was worried you'd be upset.

777
00:55:31,260 --> 00:55:32,560
Are you just going to hit me
whenever you want?

778
00:55:34,000 --> 00:55:36,370
- Watch your mouth.
- And you're so classy you use violence?

779
00:55:36,430 --> 00:55:38,330
Are you going to argue
with every single thing I say?

780
00:55:46,880 --> 00:55:47,880
I'm sorry.

781
00:55:49,950 --> 00:55:51,810
Then act like someone
I can continue to respect.

782
00:55:52,980 --> 00:55:55,320
Respect is earned through
courtesy and consideration.

783
00:55:56,290 --> 00:55:57,950
I'm the only son in my family.
You don't think this kills me?

784
00:55:58,390 --> 00:56:00,890
- It's not like you control having kids.
- That's my point.

785
00:56:05,290 --> 00:56:06,560
I told you not to swim.

786
00:56:09,830 --> 00:56:11,270
Do you have any idea
how strenuous swimming is?

787
00:56:12,400 --> 00:56:15,000
- And that's why you miscarried.
- It was fate.

788
00:56:15,540 --> 00:56:17,510
- A proper marriage...
- Fate? What nonsense is that?

789
00:56:18,840 --> 00:56:21,510
You should've been careful. It was early.

790
00:56:21,640 --> 00:56:22,880
I was trying to have a healthy baby.

791
00:56:22,950 --> 00:56:23,950
Don't make excuses.

792
00:56:24,810 --> 00:56:26,380
You took those swimming lessons
on purpose.

793
00:56:28,650 --> 00:56:29,820
I'm sick with pent-up rage, you know.

794
00:56:32,260 --> 00:56:34,520
You tell me to be Momo, but you treat me
like the old Kim Jin Ju.

795
00:56:36,230 --> 00:56:37,660
This is the last time
I'm letting this slide.

796
00:56:46,670 --> 00:56:47,740
Stop trying to be clever.

797
00:56:49,170 --> 00:56:50,210
Stop your petty little schemes.

798
00:57:15,600 --> 00:57:17,630
I'm the one in control now.

799
00:57:26,180 --> 00:57:27,180
Yong Joong.

800
00:57:29,180 --> 00:57:30,380
Are you avoiding me?

801
00:57:32,680 --> 00:57:33,680
Was what I said...

802
00:57:35,480 --> 00:57:37,120
too much for you?

803
00:57:46,930 --> 00:57:49,370
- Hello.
- I'm sorry, he's not in.

804
00:57:50,370 --> 00:57:53,270
- Is he running late?
- He's out of the country.

805
00:57:54,200 --> 00:57:56,910
- What about Pickles?
- James took him.

806
00:58:20,300 --> 00:58:21,300
Meow.

807
00:58:24,970 --> 00:58:26,070
Meow.

808
00:58:27,000 --> 00:58:28,000
Yong Joong.

809
00:58:31,610 --> 00:58:32,610
There's a little kitten.

810
00:58:34,840 --> 00:58:37,210
- How big?
- About 20cm?

811
00:58:37,850 --> 00:58:38,950
It's skin and bones.

812
00:58:51,530 --> 00:58:53,600
Did I really have to hear it
from your housekeeper...

813
00:58:53,600 --> 00:58:54,730
that you went abroad?

814
00:58:55,870 --> 00:58:57,100
Abroad?

815
00:58:57,100 --> 00:58:59,000
It was just a business trip
to a nearby country for a few days.

816
00:59:03,940 --> 00:59:04,940
You went to my place?

817
00:59:05,810 --> 00:59:06,940
Because you missed me?

818
00:59:07,910 --> 00:59:10,480
Why didn't you call?
I could've been home late.

819
00:59:11,010 --> 00:59:13,050
I didn't want to disturb you
because you're always meeting people.

820
00:59:14,880 --> 00:59:16,850
I figured the lights would just turn on
when I you got home.

821
00:59:18,620 --> 00:59:19,890
Meow.

822
00:59:21,920 --> 00:59:23,860
You know, some cats will come
and rub right up against you.

823
00:59:25,700 --> 00:59:26,760
In other countries,

824
00:59:27,260 --> 00:59:28,460
like in Europe,

825
00:59:29,530 --> 00:59:31,170
they always keep
their garden sandboxes covered.

826
00:59:31,670 --> 00:59:33,440
It's because stray cats
will use it as a litter box.

827
00:59:34,540 --> 00:59:38,110
Ever do "Pat-a-Cake?"
Have you ever played that?

828
00:59:39,080 --> 00:59:41,380
No, but I've been buried in the sand.

829
00:59:42,040 --> 00:59:44,080
- At the beach?
- Of course. Where else?

830
00:59:45,350 --> 00:59:46,450
What's it like?

831
00:59:47,180 --> 00:59:48,180
I'm curious.

832
00:59:49,090 --> 00:59:50,290
Let's go now.

833
00:59:50,350 --> 00:59:51,390
Find out for yourself.

834
00:59:51,920 --> 00:59:52,920
How?

835
00:59:53,190 --> 00:59:54,190
Why not? We have a car.

836
00:59:54,960 --> 00:59:57,360
You must be tired.
Just go home and unpack.

837
00:59:57,430 --> 00:59:59,760
I'm not tired at all,
and I have nothing to unpack.

838
00:59:59,860 --> 01:00:00,930
All I have is my carry-on.

839
01:00:04,330 --> 01:00:05,330
Want to try driving?

840
01:00:07,440 --> 01:00:08,470
This expensive car?

841
01:00:08,900 --> 01:00:10,510
There's a rest stop coming up soon.

842
01:00:11,910 --> 01:00:13,010
No way. I'm too scared.

843
01:00:13,840 --> 01:00:15,280
"A chicken instead of a pheasant."

844
01:00:15,540 --> 01:00:16,780
Momo's the one who should be here.

845
01:00:17,550 --> 01:00:18,780
Don't say that.

846
01:00:19,420 --> 01:00:22,220
You're neither a chicken nor a pheasant.
You, Geum Ba Ra, are a peacock.

847
01:00:23,490 --> 01:00:25,420
The male peacocks are the flashy ones.

848
01:00:25,690 --> 01:00:27,620
Exactly. You're not flashy.

849
01:00:29,230 --> 01:00:31,130
You're graceful and elegant.

850
01:00:33,060 --> 01:00:34,300
You're too much.

851
01:00:36,570 --> 01:00:37,770
I'm not graceful in the slightest.

852
01:00:40,840 --> 01:00:42,910
It's not about how you're dressed,
it's your aura.

853
01:00:46,010 --> 01:00:47,180
Is Momo having trouble eating?

854
01:00:49,680 --> 01:00:50,680
Morning sickness.

855
01:00:53,950 --> 01:00:55,080
She says she doesn't want to have it.

856
01:00:56,390 --> 01:00:58,390
- The baby?
- Yes.

857
01:00:58,590 --> 01:01:00,920
- Why not?
- She says she's not ready.

858
01:01:02,630 --> 01:01:03,690
But she has to.

859
01:01:07,030 --> 01:01:09,800
I saw Momo and Director Shin
at the embassy party.

860
01:01:10,070 --> 01:01:11,700
They seemed so happy.

861
01:01:12,940 --> 01:01:13,970
Which embassy?

862
01:01:14,640 --> 01:01:15,640
Arnia.

863
01:01:18,310 --> 01:01:20,010
If you're not going to drive,
why don't you get some sleep?

864
01:01:20,940 --> 01:01:22,040
Are you sure you're not tired?

865
01:01:22,550 --> 01:01:23,550
Not tired.

866
01:01:23,950 --> 01:01:27,250
Driving on an open road like this
is actually a great way to de-stress.

867
01:01:30,890 --> 01:01:33,220
You seem like the kind of person
who never gets stressed out.

868
01:01:34,060 --> 01:01:35,720
You're right. I rarely do.

869
01:01:36,090 --> 01:01:37,230
It's just not in my nature
to get stressed.

870
01:01:38,690 --> 01:01:41,200
You have no flaws. No shortcomings.

871
01:01:43,800 --> 01:01:44,970
Just one request.

872
01:01:45,940 --> 01:01:46,970
What is it?

873
01:01:46,970 --> 01:01:48,940
Don't ever shave your head
and become a monk,

874
01:01:48,940 --> 01:01:50,010
seeking enlightenment.

875
01:01:52,010 --> 01:01:53,180
Did I figure out your secret plan?

876
01:01:53,540 --> 01:01:55,010
I've never even considered it.

877
01:01:55,640 --> 01:01:57,980
I've just read a lot of books by monks,
that's all.

878
01:01:58,580 --> 01:02:00,550
Actually, not that many. Maybe 20 or so?

879
01:02:01,680 --> 01:02:04,720
Hasn't that head monk you know so well
ever suggested it?

880
01:02:05,050 --> 01:02:07,690
Head monks don't just ask anyone
to shave their head.

881
01:02:07,890 --> 01:02:11,090
They have an eye for seeing
a person's true capacity.

882
01:02:11,930 --> 01:02:14,430
He probably saw right through
my materialistic nature.

883
01:02:15,800 --> 01:02:17,130
You? Materialistic?

884
01:02:22,300 --> 01:02:23,740
I've thought about it, though.

885
01:02:24,440 --> 01:02:25,710
About becoming a nun.

886
01:02:26,710 --> 01:02:27,840
Why?

887
01:02:27,840 --> 01:02:30,010
Kids who used to bully me in school
would say...

888
01:02:31,280 --> 01:02:33,120
"Ashes, ashes, Ba Ra falls down."

889
01:02:34,020 --> 01:02:35,550
They used to tease me with that sometimes.

890
01:02:36,950 --> 01:02:38,590
I could have been born in a temple,
you know?

891
01:02:40,760 --> 01:02:41,760
No, you weren't.

892
01:02:43,260 --> 01:02:45,460
My eyes are stinging a little.
I'm just going to close them for a bit.

893
01:02:45,860 --> 01:02:46,960
Alright.

894
01:02:49,500 --> 01:02:50,500
Should I skip the rest stop?

895
01:02:51,930 --> 01:02:54,070
You have to pull the bottle away
every so often...

896
01:02:54,640 --> 01:02:57,010
and let them take a break
for a few seconds.

897
01:02:57,440 --> 01:02:59,310
Otherwise,
since they don't know any better,

898
01:02:59,680 --> 01:03:01,840
they will just guzzle it and spit it up.

899
01:03:02,180 --> 01:03:04,050
We know how exhausting it is to throw up.

900
01:03:05,350 --> 01:03:06,380
Is this who you really are?

901
01:03:06,780 --> 01:03:08,120
Do you think I'm a pushover and a joke?

902
01:03:08,120 --> 01:03:10,120
I have dignity, you know.

903
01:03:13,420 --> 01:03:15,960
(Aren't you going up?)

904
01:03:16,360 --> 01:03:19,030
(Are you going to do your rounds?)

905
01:03:30,410 --> 01:03:32,640
How long has it been
since you've been to the beach?

906
01:03:35,410 --> 01:03:37,510
The year before last for a story.

907
01:03:38,510 --> 01:03:39,520
That long ago?

908
01:03:40,620 --> 01:03:41,620
What about you?

909
01:03:42,380 --> 01:03:43,390
Last month.

910
01:03:43,890 --> 01:03:46,660
I just come here on a whim
whenever I have something on my mind.

911
01:03:48,590 --> 01:03:52,130
I guess he didn't need to come here
just to think about what I said.

912
01:03:57,570 --> 01:03:59,130
I think they maintain the sand here.

913
01:03:59,440 --> 01:04:01,770
It's always clean.
There aren't even any seashells.

914
01:04:13,550 --> 01:04:14,920
Speaking of regrets,

915
01:04:15,880 --> 01:04:16,890
I do have one.

916
01:04:18,950 --> 01:04:19,990
My dad and I...

917
01:04:20,690 --> 01:04:22,660
never got to play catch. Not even once.

918
01:04:25,060 --> 01:04:26,260
He was always so busy.

919
01:04:29,260 --> 01:04:31,000
Doing it at a beach like this...

920
01:04:31,870 --> 01:04:33,040
would've been so nice.

921
01:04:36,440 --> 01:04:39,810
Nine is too young to lose your father.

922
01:04:40,680 --> 01:04:41,680
Tell me about it.

923
01:04:45,810 --> 01:04:48,550
So I can't even imagine
what it's like for you.

924
01:04:55,960 --> 01:04:58,260
When you look at those waves
endlessly crashing on the shore,

925
01:04:58,990 --> 01:05:00,060
what comes to mind?

926
01:05:03,600 --> 01:05:05,100
Right now, nothing.

927
01:05:07,300 --> 01:05:09,610
It just feels refreshing to watch them.

928
01:05:10,510 --> 01:05:11,610
Does it help you feel a little lighter?

929
01:05:15,510 --> 01:05:17,250
What about you? What comes to mind?

930
01:05:19,920 --> 01:05:22,220
They remind me of the adversities
we face in life.

931
01:05:24,220 --> 01:05:26,990
You get over one hurdle,
and there's another.

932
01:05:28,660 --> 01:05:31,290
I suppose my waves have been
relatively calm,

933
01:05:31,560 --> 01:05:32,560
so far, at least.

934
01:05:36,030 --> 01:05:39,070
But you, Ba Ra, from a very early age...

935
01:05:39,970 --> 01:05:41,940
were hit by a tidal wave,

936
01:05:43,410 --> 01:05:44,940
but you weren't swept away. You held on.

937
01:05:46,910 --> 01:05:47,980
I'm so incredibly proud of you.

938
01:05:52,750 --> 01:05:53,750
When I was in Japan,

939
01:05:55,980 --> 01:05:57,490
I thought long and hard
about what you said...

940
01:05:59,190 --> 01:06:00,390
Where is my head?

941
01:06:00,390 --> 01:06:01,690
What's wrong with me?

942
01:06:01,690 --> 01:06:03,530
- What is it?
- It's in the car!

943
01:06:12,070 --> 01:06:13,900
- For today...
- You don't need to show us.

944
01:06:14,240 --> 01:06:15,240
All right.

945
01:06:17,570 --> 01:06:18,970
How are you so good with babies?

946
01:06:19,480 --> 01:06:21,110
Try asking what I'm not good at.

947
01:07:02,080 --> 01:07:03,350
I left it in the trunk.

948
01:07:07,020 --> 01:07:08,390
You brought this just for me?

949
01:07:08,790 --> 01:07:09,790
Of course. Who else?

950
01:07:17,370 --> 01:07:20,070
- You probably can't smell it by the sea.
- I can.

951
01:07:20,540 --> 01:07:23,070
That explains it. On the drive here,
I wondered if you bought a perfume.

952
01:07:24,070 --> 01:07:25,870
I didn't get you any
because I didn't think you wore perfume.

953
01:07:26,380 --> 01:07:28,040
That's because I don't have any to wear.

954
01:07:28,640 --> 01:07:29,710
I'll buy you some first thing tomorrow.

955
01:07:30,010 --> 01:07:31,810
I'm just kidding. I don't wear any.

956
01:07:33,080 --> 01:07:34,450
I hope the cream didn't melt.

957
01:07:34,780 --> 01:07:37,350
It should be fine.
Look, they put an ice pack in.

958
01:07:45,860 --> 01:07:47,300
I'm sorry it took me this long
to give you flowers.

959
01:07:48,500 --> 01:07:50,030
I should have given them to you first.

960
01:07:50,800 --> 01:07:54,270
It's not like big brothers usually do this
for their little sisters, anyway.

961
01:07:57,170 --> 01:07:59,070
Even now, that first time we met
in front of the supermarket...

962
01:08:00,440 --> 01:08:01,840
feels like only yesterday.

963
01:08:01,840 --> 01:08:03,410
Your eyes were just filled with tears.

964
01:08:04,950 --> 01:08:07,620
Just forget it.
It's not exactly a good memory.

965
01:08:08,480 --> 01:08:10,090
It's not about whether
it's a good or bad memory.

966
01:08:12,120 --> 01:08:13,860
When I think about
what you said back then,

967
01:08:15,060 --> 01:08:16,330
my heart just aches.

968
01:08:18,590 --> 01:08:20,560
I realize I never truly understood
what you were going through.

969
01:08:21,130 --> 01:08:22,530
And I'm supposed to be
the one closest to you.

970
01:08:28,070 --> 01:08:29,070
Aren't I?

971
01:08:30,610 --> 01:08:31,610
You are.

972
01:08:32,610 --> 01:08:33,880
It wasn't that I was being insensitive.

973
01:08:35,240 --> 01:08:36,650
It was just that instead of
a small gift like a cake,

974
01:08:37,310 --> 01:08:39,680
I wanted to do something
so much better for you.

975
01:08:47,320 --> 01:08:48,390
To me...

976
01:08:50,990 --> 01:08:52,430
you're not a little kid anymore.

977
01:08:54,960 --> 01:08:56,230
And at some point,

978
01:08:58,370 --> 01:09:00,100
I started to see you in a different light.

979
01:09:56,690 --> 01:09:59,590
(Doctor Shin)

980
01:09:59,830 --> 01:10:01,660
- Thank you.
- Are you her stylist?

981
01:10:01,730 --> 01:10:02,730
I'm still just an assistant.

982
01:10:02,800 --> 01:10:06,200
If Ba Ra finds out it's me and not Momo,
she is going to flip out.

983
01:10:06,270 --> 01:10:09,170
Since you've decided,
can't you just do it once?

984
01:10:09,240 --> 01:10:10,310
If you come with me,

985
01:10:11,110 --> 01:10:12,240
I'll go three times instead of twice.

986
01:10:12,770 --> 01:10:15,140
- Four times?
- I'll go with you every single time.

987
01:10:15,210 --> 01:10:17,610
He might want to get rid of me,

988
01:10:17,610 --> 01:10:19,180
but he can't just take out the brain.

989
01:10:19,250 --> 01:10:21,150
To get rid of me, he'd have to kill Momo.

990
01:10:21,150 --> 01:10:23,220
Could he kill Momo and get away with it?

991
01:10:23,350 --> 01:10:24,350
Do you like Director Shin?

992
01:10:24,620 --> 01:10:26,050
I used to have feelings for him.

993
01:10:26,190 --> 01:10:29,830
- Grandpa says she died and came back.
- From the dead?

994
01:10:29,890 --> 01:10:33,630
To Kim Jin Ju, Director Shin is
a deity or her Prince Charming.

995
01:10:33,700 --> 01:10:34,760
But now it's my turn.

996
01:10:36,030 --> 01:10:37,600
- Hey, James.
- Get over here, quick!

997
01:10:37,670 --> 01:10:39,170
- What's wrong?
- What am I going to do?

998
01:10:41,640 --> 01:10:42,740
My first love is...

999
01:10:43,000 --> 01:10:44,210
Ba Ra.

1000
01:10:47,210 --> 01:10:49,210
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
